Parks Library.description: The ISU Public Library is a place for students to go to quietly work and study while on campus.

Memorial Union.description: The Memorial Union is a public place with multitudes of student services and activities.

Student Innovation Center.description: The Student Innovation Center is a place where students imagine, create, and of course innovate.

Beardshear Hall.description: Beardshear Hall is the place that new students should become familiar with as that's where most of their in-person registration is.

Maple, Willow, Larch Residence Halls.description: Maple, Willow, and Larch are all residence halls perfect for incoming students.

State Gym.description: The State Gym is a great centralized place for students to work out and exercise.

Lied Recreation Center.description: The Lied Rec Center is another gym placed to the north of Maple, Willow, and Larch, a good starting gym for those new students.

Campanile.description: In the center of campus lies the Campanile. Being one of the major symbols of Iowa State as well as the university's alma mater.

Curtiss Hall.description: Curtiss Hall, first called Agriculture Hall, is the hub of Agricultural knowledge and exams.

Simon Estes Music Hall.description: Simon Estes Music Hall is the place where music majors gather to learn. Additionally, concerts and final performances of the students are played here.

Jack Trice Stadium.description: Jack Trice Stadium is the place to go for football games. Eager fans pack the seats and pridefully cheer for their side.

Hilton Coliseum.description: Hilton Coliseum is the place to go to see the upcoming basketball or volleyball game.

Stephens Auditorium.description: The most matching place for a musical menagerie to monger and mingle or man and mouse to meet and mask onstage might materialize at Stephens Auditorium.
